President Barack Obama has appointed Jodi Gillette as Senior Policy Advisor for Native American Affairs. As a member of the Domestic Policy Council, Gillette will advise the President on issues impacting Indian Country. Gillette, an enrolled member of the Standing Rock Sioux Tribe, has previously held positions in the U.S. Department of the Interior and the White House. She has played a key role in organizing the White House Tribal Nations Conference and has a background in economic development and public policy.